This article summarizes remarks made by President Trump and other officials during a meeting in the Oval Office. The President and First Lady express their support for the Special Olympics and thank Vice President Pence and Karen Pence for their involvement. The CEO of the Special Olympics, Mary Davis, speaks about the impact of the athletes in representing the United States and building diplomatic relations. The President congratulates the athletes on their accomplishments and discusses his views on various topics, including Iran, the NAACP, and recent chants at his rallies. He also addresses the debt ceiling and the possibility of sanctions on Turkey.